To-Do App

A simple and modern To-Do List web application built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
The app allows users to add tasks, mark them as completed, and delete them when finished. All tasks are saved in localStorage, so they stay even after refreshing the page.

Features

Add new tasks

Mark tasks as completed using a checkbox

Delete tasks

Tasks are saved in the browser using localStorage

Clean and responsive user interface

Custom styled checkboxes and icons

Technologies Used

HTML – Structure of the application

CSS – Styling and layout

JavaScript  – Functionality and task management

Local Storage – Saving tasks in the browser

Project Structure
todo-app/
│
├── index.html     # Main HTML file
├── style.css      # Styling for the app
├── app.js         # JavaScript functionality
└── README.md      # Project documentation
How to Use the App

Open the application

Download or clone the project.

Open the index.html file in your web browser.

Add a task

Type a task in the input field.

Press Enter or click the Add button.

Mark a task as completed

Click the checkbox next to the task.

The task will be marked as completed.

Delete a task

Click the trash icon next to the task.

The task will be removed from the list.

Automatic saving

All tasks are automatically saved in your browser using localStorage.

When you refresh the page, your tasks will still be there.


